criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  circulatory and respiratory stability;

          -  readiness for oral feeding according to each child's Speech-Language Pathologist
             assessment;

          -  prematurely born infants who were in the process of being transferred from enteral
             nutrition (or enteral nutrition + parenteral nutrition) to full oral feeding and were
             fed orally at least 4- 6 times within twenty-four hours;

          -  parents gave informed consent to participate their infant in the study.

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  disorders which could significantly affect the feeding course, such as cleft lip
             and/or palate, facial paralysis and/or congenital defects of the facial skeleton;

          -  the presence of detected congenital abnormalities and metabolic diseases; low Apgar
             score (less than 5 points at the 5th and 10th minute of the measurement);

          -  administered analgesics, anticonvulsants and sedatives;

          -  <72 hours from extubation prior the trial;

          -  parents refusal to participate in the study or when bottle-feeding was not the
             parental preference.
